CatDescriptText: Clark's Delicatessen at 2101 Webster Avenue, Hill District, belonged to John S. Clark in 1951.  In the window are advertisements for Meadow Gold Ice Cream, Masons Root Beer, Cavalier Cigarettes, and Camel Cigarettes.  The deli offers fruits, vegetables, lunch meats, candy, and fountain service.
TitMainTitle: Clark's Delicatessen, John Clark, proprietor, at 2101 Webster Avenue at corner of Erin Street
